text: when the commission granted texas eastern authority to hold capacity on another pipeline in texas eastern transmission corporation, 74 ferc p 61,074 (1996), it stated that when a pipeline holds capacity on an upstream pipeline, the downstream pipeline's customers may hold title to the gas transported on the upstream pipeline.

text: the commission recognized this as one of the limited exceptions to the shipper must have title rule.
label: None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None

text: specifically, the commission stated: the downstream pipeline will not hold title to gas shipped on capacity it has acquired on an upstream pipeline.
label: None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None

text: rather, shippers on the downstream pipeline will hold title to the gas on the upstream pipeline.
label: None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None

text: we will allow a pipeline to hold the upstream capacity; we will not, however, allow the pipeline to hold title to the gas being shipped.
label: None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None

text: thus, the downstream pipeline will be the shipper on the upstream pipeline, but will not hold title when the gas is being shipped.
